<td>Three</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Rak</td>
<td>Four</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Nes</td>
<td>Five</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Yor</td>
<td>Six</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>My</td>
<td>Seven</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Additional concepts in Ortothan mathematics include:</p>
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<th>Concept/Number</th>
<th>Definition</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Forta</td>
<td><a href="/scp-033">Banished for crimes unspoken.</a> The Koru-teusa's reasons are not known but we trust in them.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Nen-Exten</td>
<td>Literally &quot;zero-infinities,&quot; sapient mathematical constructs enlisted in calculations that minds and computers are incapable or ordinarily processing. The summoning of them is not recommend for Ortothans unfamiliar with basic 4+ dimensional arithmetic or aversions to math &#8212; they will judge.</td>
</tr>
</table>
